1.6
log
@Where a program with an rc script _requires_ a certain command line
parameter to daemonize, move the parameter from daemon to daemon_flags,
so that the user cannot inadvertently prevent it from daemonizing by
adjusting the flags.

Discussed with ajacoutot and schwarze, this method was suggested
by schwarze@@ as a simpler alternative to my diff. ok aja@@
@
text
@#!/bin/sh
#
# $OpenBSD: polipo.rc,v 1.5 2010/12/27 14:50:24 ajacoutot Exp $

daemon="${TRUEPREFIX}/bin/polipo daemonise=yes"

. /etc/rc.d/rc.subr

rc_reload=NO

rc_cmd $1
@


1.5
log
@Simplify after recent rc.subr change.
The framework is now stable and we will start documenting it (at last).
@
text
@d3 1
a3 1
# $OpenBSD: polipo.rc,v 1.4 2010/12/24 10:40:06 ajacoutot Exp $
d5 1
a5 2
daemon="${TRUEPREFIX}/bin/polipo"
daemon_flags="daemonise=yes"
@


1.4
log
@Cope with recent rc.subr changes.
@
text
@d3 1
a3 3
# $OpenBSD: polipo.rc,v 1.3 2010/12/11 12:57:37 ajacoutot Exp $

. /etc/rc.d/rc.subr
d8 1
a8 1
rc_conf
@


